38/**
39 * DOC: uevents generated by i915 on it's device node
40 *
41 * I915_L3_PARITY_UEVENT - Generated when the driver receives a parity mismatch
42 * event from the gpu l3 cache. Additional information supplied is ROW,
43 * BANK, SUBBANK, SLICE of the affected cacheline. Userspace should keep
44 * track of these events and if a specific cache-line seems to have a
45 * persistent error remap it with the l3 remapping tool supplied in
46 * intel-gpu-tools. The value supplied with the event is always 1.
47 *
48 * I915_ERROR_UEVENT - Generated upon error detection, currently only via
49 * hangcheck. The error detection event is a good indicator of when things
50 * began to go badly. The value supplied with the event is a 1 upon error
51 * detection, and a 0 upon reset completion, signifying no more error
52 * exists. NOTE: Disabling hangcheck or reset via module parameter will
53 * cause the related events to not be seen.
54 *
55 * I915_RESET_UEVENT - Event is generated just before an attempt to reset the
56 * the GPU. The value supplied with the event is always 1. NOTE: Disable
57 * reset via module parameter will cause this event to not be seen.
58 */
59#define I915_L3_PARITY_UEVENT "L3_PARITY_ERROR"
60#define I915_ERROR_UEVENT "ERROR"
61#define I915_RESET_UEVENT "RESET"
62
63/* Each region is a minimum of 16k, and there are at most 255 of them.
64 */
65#define I915_NR_TEX_REGIONS 255 /* table size 2k - maximum due to use
66 * of chars for next/prev indices */
67#define I915_LOG_MIN_TEX_REGION_SIZE 14

69typedef struct _drm_i915_init {
70 enum {
71 I915_INIT_DMA = 0x01,
72 I915_CLEANUP_DMA = 0x02,
73 I915_RESUME_DMA = 0x03
74 } func;
75 unsigned int mmio_offset;
76 int sarea_priv_offset;
77 unsigned int ring_start;
78 unsigned int ring_end;
79 unsigned int ring_size;
80 unsigned int front_offset;
81 unsigned int back_offset;
82 unsigned int depth_offset;
83 unsigned int w;
84 unsigned int h;
85 unsigned int pitch;
86 unsigned int pitch_bits;
87 unsigned int back_pitch;
88 unsigned int depth_pitch;
89 unsigned int cpp;
90 unsigned int chipset;
91} drm_i915_init_t;

93typedef struct _drm_i915_sarea {
94 struct drm_tex_region texList[I915_NR_TEX_REGIONS + 1];
95 int last_upload; /* last time texture was uploaded */
96 int last_enqueue; /* last time a buffer was enqueued */
97 int last_dispatch; /* age of the most recently dispatched buffer */
98 int ctxOwner; /* last context to upload state */
99 int texAge;
100 int pf_enabled; /* is pageflipping allowed? */
101 int pf_active;
102 int pf_current_page; /* which buffer is being displayed? */
103 int perf_boxes; /* performance boxes to be displayed */
104 int width, height; /* screen size in pixels */
105
106 drm_handle_t front_handle;
107 int front_offset;
108 int front_size;
109
110 drm_handle_t back_handle;
111 int back_offset;
112 int back_size;
113
114 drm_handle_t depth_handle;
115 int depth_offset;
116 int depth_size;
117
118 drm_handle_t tex_handle;
119 int tex_offset;
120 int tex_size;
121 int log_tex_granularity;
122 int pitch;
123 int rotation; /* 0, 90, 180 or 270 */
124 int rotated_offset;
125 int rotated_size;
126 int rotated_pitch;
127 int virtualX, virtualY;
128
129 unsigned int front_tiled;
130 unsigned int back_tiled;
131 unsigned int depth_tiled;
132 unsigned int rotated_tiled;
133 unsigned int rotated2_tiled;
134
135 int pipeA_x;
136 int pipeA_y;
137 int pipeA_w;
138 int pipeA_h;
139 int pipeB_x;
140 int pipeB_y;
141 int pipeB_w;
142 int pipeB_h;
143
144 /* fill out some space for old userspace triple buffer */
145 drm_handle_t unused_handle;
146 __u32 unused1, unused2, unused3;
147
148 /* buffer object handles for static buffers. May change
149 * over the lifetime of the client.
150 */
151 __u32 front_bo_handle;
152 __u32 back_bo_handle;
153 __u32 unused_bo_handle;
154 __u32 depth_bo_handle;
155
156} drm_i915_sarea_t;

176/*
177 * i915 specific ioctls.
178 *
179 * The device specific ioctl range is [DRM_COMMAND_BASE, DRM_COMMAND_END) ie
180 * [0x40, 0xa0) (a0 is excluded). The numbers below are defined as offset
181 * against DRM_COMMAND_BASE and should be between [0x0, 0x60).
182 */

289/* Allow drivers to submit batchbuffers directly to hardware, relying
290 * on the security mechanisms provided by hardware.
291 */
292typedef struct drm_i915_batchbuffer {
293 int start; /* agp offset */
294 int used; /* nr bytes in use */
295 int DR1; /* hw flags for GFX_OP_DRAWRECT_INFO */
296 int DR4; /* window origin for GFX_OP_DRAWRECT_INFO */
297 int num_cliprects; /* mulitpass with multiple cliprects? */
298 struct drm_clip_rect __user *cliprects; /* pointer to userspace cliprects */
299} drm_i915_batchbuffer_t;
300
301/* As above, but pass a pointer to userspace buffer which can be
302 * validated by the kernel prior to sending to hardware.
303 */
304typedef struct _drm_i915_cmdbuffer {
305 char __user *buf; /* pointer to userspace command buffer */
306 int sz; /* nr bytes in buf */
307 int DR1; /* hw flags for GFX_OP_DRAWRECT_INFO */
308 int DR4; /* window origin for GFX_OP_DRAWRECT_INFO */
309 int num_cliprects; /* mulitpass with multiple cliprects? */
310 struct drm_clip_rect __user *cliprects; /* pointer to userspace cliprects */
311} drm_i915_cmdbuffer_t;

433struct drm_i915_gem_init {
434 /**
435 * Beginning offset in the GTT to be managed by the DRM memory
436 * manager.

439 /**
440 * Ending offset in the GTT to be managed by the DRM memory
441 * manager.

443 __u64 gtt_end;
444};

446struct drm_i915_gem_create {
447 /**
448 * Requested size for the object.
449 *
450 * The (page-aligned) allocated size for the object will be returned.
451 */
452 __u64 size;
453 /**
454 * Returned handle for the object.
455 *
456 * Object handles are nonzero.
457 */
458 __u32 handle;
459 __u32 pad;
460};
461
462struct drm_i915_gem_pread {
463 /** Handle for the object being read. */
464 __u32 handle;
465 __u32 pad;
466 /** Offset into the object to read from */
467 __u64 offset;
468 /** Length of data to read */
469 __u64 size;
470 /**
471 * Pointer to write the data into.
472 *
473 * This is a fixed-size type for 32/64 compatibility.
474 */
475 __u64 data_ptr;
476};
477
478struct drm_i915_gem_pwrite {
479 /** Handle for the object being written to. */
480 __u32 handle;
481 __u32 pad;

819/**
820 * I915_CACHING_NONE
821 *
822 * GPU access is not coherent with cpu caches. Default for machines without an
823 * LLC.
824 */
825#define I915_CACHING_NONE 0
826/**
827 * I915_CACHING_CACHED
828 *
829 * GPU access is coherent with cpu caches and furthermore the data is cached in
830 * last-level caches shared between cpu cores and the gpu GT. Default on
831 * machines with HAS_LLC.
832 */
833#define I915_CACHING_CACHED 1
834/**
835 * I915_CACHING_DISPLAY
836 *
837 * Special GPU caching mode which is coherent with the scanout engines.
838 * Transparently falls back to I915_CACHING_NONE on platforms where no special
839 * cache mode (like write-through or gfdt flushing) is available. The kernel
840 * automatically sets this mode when using a buffer as a scanout target.
841 * Userspace can manually set this mode to avoid a costly stall and clflush in
842 * the hotpath of drawing the first frame.
843 */
844#define I915_CACHING_DISPLAY 2

1032/*
1033 * Intel sprite handling
1034 *
1035 * Color keying works with a min/mask/max tuple. Both source and destination
1036 * color keying is allowed.
1037 *
1038 * Source keying:
1039 * Sprite pixels within the min & max values, masked against the color channels
1040 * specified in the mask field, will be transparent. All other pixels will
1041 * be displayed on top of the primary plane. For RGB surfaces, only the min
1042 * and mask fields will be used; ranged compares are not allowed.
1043 *
1044 * Destination keying:
1045 * Primary plane pixels that match the min value, masked against the color
1046 * channels specified in the mask field, will be replaced by corresponding
1047 * pixels from the sprite plane.
1048 *
1049 * Note that source & destination keying are exclusive; only one can be
1050 * active on a given plane.
1051 */
1052
1053#define I915_SET_COLORKEY_NONE (1<<0) /* disable color key matching */
1054#define I915_SET_COLORKEY_DESTINATION (1<<1)
1055#define I915_SET_COLORKEY_SOURCE (1<<2)
1056struct drm_intel_sprite_colorkey {
1057 __u32 plane_id;
1058 __u32 min_value;
1059 __u32 channel_mask;
1060 __u32 max_value;
1061 __u32 flags;
1062};
